    <h1>Round Body</h1>

    <h2>Round Body Type for Females</h2>

    <h3>Body Type Description</h3>
    <p>The round body type, often referred to as the endomorph body type, is characterized by a softer, rounder appearance with a higher percentage of body fat and a wider waist. Women with this body type tend to store fat in the lower body, such as the hips, thighs, and buttocks, and may have a fuller bust. This body type typically has a wider bone structure and can gain weight easily, but they can also build muscle effectively with the right training and diet.</p>

    <h3>Food List for Round Body Type Females</h3>
    <p>To support weight management and muscle retention, a balanced diet rich in whole, nutrient-dense foods is essential. The recommended macronutrient breakdown for round body types is generally 30% carbs, 40% protein, and 30% fat.</p>

